						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone built into the northern prākāra (inside) of the Vīranārāyaṇa temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Indra III—A.D. 918.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Nityavarsha Indara Vallaha</hi> and is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 840, Bahudhānya, Śrāvaṇa, śu. 7, Sunday,</hi> probably corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 918, July 18;</hi> the week-day was <hi rend="bold">Saturday.</hi> It seems to register a settlement made regarding the revenue of <hi rend="bold">Baṭṭakeṛe</hi> between <hi rend="bold">Mahāśrīmanta,</hi> the governor of <hi rend="bold">Beḷvala Three-hundred</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of the place. A certain <hi rend="bold">Dāmapayya</hi> is mentioned. </p>						

						</summary>
